  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/botany/terms/tropism/> ;
  schema:name "Tropism" ;
  schema:description "A tropism is a directional growth or movement response of an organism to an environmental stimulus. The term derives from the Greek *tropos* (turning). Phototropism is growth toward or away from light; gravitropism is growth in response to gravity; thigmotropism is growth in response to touch; chemotropism is growth in response to chemical gradients." ;
